{
  "text": "Bosakowski and Wagner [CITATION_1] found that density and environmental conditions were significantly related to fin erosion. Furthermore, Arctic charr fed in excess and allowed to haphazardly swim in their tanks had increased aggressive behavior and damaged fins [CITATION_2] . It was expected that fish in the 0.5 BL/s would exhibit increased aggressive behavior resulting in increased fin erosion, but this did not occur. The lack of significant differences in fin erosion among the treatments likely indicates a relative lack of environmental stress and a lack of aggressive behavior.",
  "correct_citation": {
